@NODE "Mail_0" " A replacement for the bad blitz Timer fonction. "
From: Benjamin VERNOUX <bvernoux@kyxar.fr>
Date: 03-06-00 19:41:56
Subject: @{b}A replacement for the bad blitz Timer fonction.@{ub}

Hi, all

I have write two new fonctions in a blitz library for replace the bad blitz
Timer fonction, it's very good for make multiple time, clock or other in
multitask and it's totaly independant of the PAL or NTSC display.
If you want the asm source code of this lib i can attach it later.

The attached lib contain two fonctions, the first named clockAll who work on
all 68k processors and an other who is named clock, who's optimized for
68020, 030, 040 and 060 processors.
I have attached also 2 examples and there source code.  

For installing this lib copy it on blitzlibs:userlibs/
and launch makedeflibs or other.

WARNING don't launch the example from WB !!
You must launch the examples on CLI and stop it with Ctrl C.  

Bye
