It will still be in Blitz mode, because the BLITZ command is not only 
a compiler directive, but it actually does things too (turns off 
multitasking etc). You'll probably get errors when trying to execute 
the commands between the label1: and the BLITZ command, because these 
will have been compiled as the AMIGA mode versions, but you are 
trying to execute them in BLITZ mode.

