> Blitz Libraries BLoad and BSave commands. E.g.:

Sequential file is just a hype of higher programming languages. There are no
different file "types". OS handless all files equally. So you can seek and
write all kind of stuff for your random access file or sequential text
file and OS just doesn't care.

The only thing for binary files is that reading can't be done with edit$()
because it doesn't get the linefeeds etc line separator characters to the
string it returns.

So for file copy:

#memfany=0
#bufsize=4096

buf.l=AllocMem_(#bufsize,#memfany)

If buf<>0
  If OpenFile(0,"where")
	If OpenFile(1,"towhere")

	  l.l=Lof(0)
	  ll.l=l/#bufsize
	  l=l-(ll*#bufsize)
	  While ll>0
		ReadMem 0,buf,#bufsize
		WriteMem 1,buf,#bufsize
		ll-1
	  Wend
	  ReadMem 0,buf,l
	  WriteMem 1,buf,l
	  CloseFile 1
	EndIf
	CloseFile 0
  EndIf
  FreeMem_ buf,#bufsize
EndIf
End

If not wanting to use any blitz commands then simply
use the OS ones. (With the OS thing you have to so the seeks by yourself,
so it needs litle bit more from the code)

