On 24-Mar-00, David McMinn wrote.

> just noticed a command in the displaylib: DisplayDblScan. Anyone tried
> this? Does it actually do a 31kHz type display?

No it will do doublescaned display. Meaning that you can use 128 pixel high
bitmap to fill 256 scan lines or even 64 pixel high can be quadscaned to
fill the 256 line high display. This is usefull in the situations where you
want to show animation in full screen, but do not have enough speed or
memory to decode such animation. So instead you can use half heighted
animation, but still manage to get the same height without black lines
in between. The black lines trick was used on some early day demos and game
intros.

