Sorry I typed all this in and then realised you said simple solution. Which it 
might be depending on your programming skills.

You could use the intuition gadget help messages (OS3+). There's a small delay 
after you stop moving the mouse before you get the message and you will only 
get one message until you move the mouse again.

You'll need to do something like this:

helpgroup.l = GetUniqueID_

Dim wtags.TagItem(10)
wtags(0)\ti_Tag=#WA_Left,100
wtags(1)\ti_Tag=#WA_Top,100
wtags(2)\ti_Tag=#WA_Width,300
wtags(3)\ti_Tag=#WA_Height,200
wtags(4)\ti_Tag=#WA_HelpGroup,helpgroup
wtags(5)\ti_Tag=#TAG_DONE

AddIDCMP #IDCMP_GADGETHELP
WindowTags 0,$100f,"title",&wtags(0)
DefaultOutput
HelpControl_ Peek.l(Addr Window(0)),#HC_GADGETHELP

While ev.l<>#IDCMP_CLOSEWINDOW
	ev=WaitEvent
	if ev=#IDCMP_GADGETHELP
		*g.Gadget=EventIAddress
		if *g=0
			NPrint "mouse not over window"
		else
			if *g=peek.l(addr window(0))
				nprint "over window, but not gadget"
			else
				if *g\GadgetType & #GTYP_SYSGADGET
					nprint "over system gadget of window"
				else
					nprint "mouse over gadget #",*g\GadgetID
				end if
			end if
		end if
	end if
Wend

