relative to the current address. So you should be able to Gosub and 
Return from anywhere in memory.

Make sure you haven't done something like this:


; blah, main program here
; blah more main program

; subroutine
blah:
; blah blah blah
return

End

Because the subroutine will be executed as the program runs through 
the main program and when it hits the return it won't have been 
gosub'bed to.

> I've worked around it by moving the subroutine nearer to the
> Gosub,but is there anything else I should know? Does this happen
> with functions? (I suppose not) 

No, and it shouldn't happen with gosubs either.


