were GoSubbing to an AmigaMode section of code from a BlitzMode section, or
something like that?

That won't work either, as David pointed out, since some commands are
compiled differently for the different modes.

Once you use the command:

"Blitz" 

everything after that in your code will be compiled for Blitz mode until you
enter the command:

"Amiga"

So any subroutines in that section should only be accessed while in Blitz
mode.

You could do something like this:

;main program code here

end

;subroutines section

Blitz

; all Blitzmode subroutines go here

Amiga

; all Amigamode subroutines go here





