Hi George

>  How many times can you nest Gosubs? (if there's a limit)

No no, no no no no, no no there's no limit. Sorry.

>  Could it be running out of stack space?

Yes.

>  How can you increase the program's stack space?

You can do it within your program using StackSwap_ command, although 
Rob H has done some simple functions for this in the MUI2.res file 
(http://www.satanicdreams.com).

The stack size of Blitz2 is the stack that your program gets when it 
is run from the editor, so either increase the stack size on the CLI 
or in the Blitz2 icon.

Obviously when running your own exe, increase the stack size in the 
CLI or the icon.

>  Is there anything else I should know about nesting Subroutines?

make sure you are using gosub...return, not goto...return.

make sure you are not screwing up with "Pop".

If...EndIf, For...Next, and all the other loops are limited to 32k in 
size. Its difficult to go above this thought, unless you really go 
for it.

