I think I see what you are trying to do - put a variable - length string
right into the NewType?  If that is it, sorry, but it is truly
impossible...

A NewType (or structure, if you want to use the "C" terminology) is simply a
pre-defined block of memory, and accessed in the same way you would access
the records on a random-access disk file.

So, an array of your NewType in memory is very similar to a random-access
file in memory.  Each NewType must be the exact same length, just as a
random-access disk file has a fixed length for each field...

You can't define it with an un-specified overall size for each record...  

