Don't forget to add this line first:

DosBuffLen 0  ;use no buffers for writing to CON: or PRT: for immediate
output!

This is necessary because otherwise Blitz will use the default buffersize
(2048, I think) and if your string is shorter than this, you won't see
anything in your console window until you close the "file" and Blitz
flushes the buffer, which in this case would mean nothing would show until
you closed the console window...

Set it back to 2048 or whatever using the same command before accessing an
actual disk file.

