@NODE "Mail_280" " Re: Trobles with GTCycle "
From: Nick Lamburn <oruk-amigan@free4all.co.uk>
Date: 03-04-00 16:03:46
Subject: @{b}Re: Trobles with GTCycle@{ub}

Hello 

>    I've started to write small program which has to be GUI for variety
> pack programs. It based on GTgadgets. I used GTCycles but I have problem
> with read which one options is active at the moment. I've read about
> #GTCY_Active, but : 1) I'm not sure if it is that what I'm looking for 2)
> I don't know how to use this (if the answer for question 1 is true)

Okay, this is quite a normal problem, which Indeed I had when I first
started with Blitz some many moons ago! :)  What you need to use is a
command called EventCode, this will tell you which item is active in a Cycle
gadget (and Listview, Radio, Slider etc.).

Okay here's an example:
-------------------
#WBStartup ; make program run for wbench#
#WBToScreen 0 ; use wbench screen#

#; now create a gadtools cycler
##GTCycle 0,0,100,20,100,15,"Cycle:",0,"Waffles|Pizza|Eggs|Bread|Beans"#
##
#Window 0,0,0,300,100,$4|$8|$400|$1000,"My Window",2,1
#AttachGTList 0,0 ; stick gtlist 0 on window 0
#
#Repeat
#    ev.l=WaitEvent ; wait for an event to happen
#    code.b=EventCode ; get the event's code

#    Select ev
#        Case $8
#            quit.b=true
#        Case $40
#            Select GadgetHit
#                Case 0
#                    Select code
#                        Case 0
#                            WTitle "Waffles Selected"
#                        Case 1
#                            WTitle "Pizza Selected"
#                        Case 2
#                            WTitle "Eggs Selected"
#                        case 3
#                            WTitle "Bread Selected"
#                        Case 4
#                            WTitle "Beans"
#                    End Select
#            End Select
#    End Select
#Until quit=True

#CloseWindow 0
#Free GTList 0
#End
-------------------
Basically the main code is a loop which checks the events, $40 is gadget hit
and that's the code the cycle gadget will send to your window's event port
(techy name: IDCMP Message Port :), the select blocks find which gadget was
hit, and then what code was sent.  The code is the item selected in the
cycle gadget and the Window should change its title to reflect the current
item selected.

The #GTCY_ACTIVE 'tag' is used to specify which item is currently active in
the cycle gadget to begin with.  This means that you could have 'Beans',
'Eggs' and 'Nappies' as choices, but instead of having Beans selected when
you start you could have Eggs or Nappies selected.

To use that feature, before you /initialise /the cycle gadget or call the
CTCycle command you would insert:

#GTTags #GTCY_Active,1#

That would make the second item active in the list.  Make sure that you have
BLITZLIBS:AmigaLibs.res specified in the compiler options window.

Good luck and I hope this helps! :)

Kind Regards

Nick.
