@NODE "Mail_304" " Re: Windows to Bitmap ? "
From: David McMinn <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Date: 03-14-00 11:11:05
Subject: @{b}Re: Windows to Bitmap ?@{ub}

Hi Pearl

> I beg your pardon for this stupid question, but how can I copy the Bitmap of
> a window in an other bitmap without using SuperBitmaps ?

Its not a stupid question, as the manuals only ever show you how to 
copy from a bitmap to a window and not the other way round.

> I want to do something like this:
> 
>     Window 0,0,0,300,200, ...
>     Bitmap 1,300,200,4
>     CopyBitmap RastPort(0),1

Window 0,0,0,300,200, ...
*win.Window = Peek.l(Addr Window(0))
BitMap 1,300,200,4
BltBitMap_ *win\RPort\BitMap,0,0,Addr 
BitMap(1),0,0,300,200,$c0,$ffff,0

my mailer may have wrapped those last two lines.


